    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "Available for acquisition is a 2004 BMW M3 (E46) featuring the high-revving S54 3.2L inline-six power plant. This engine utilizes individual throttle bodies and a dual-VANOS variable valve timing system to deliver a linear power band peaking at its 8,000 RPM redline. Power is managed via a Getrag 6-speed manual gearbox and transmitted through a variable M-differential lock. The chassis maintains high torsional rigidity, having undergone proactive rear subframe reinforcement to mitigate floor pan fatigue. Suspension geometry remains stock with MacPherson struts and a multi-link rear setup, though bushings have been refreshed to maintain factory damping characteristics. Recent mechanical overhead includes a comprehensive valve adjustment and rod bearing replacement, ensuring the reciprocating assembly is within factory tolerances. The exterior presents with minor road patina, while the interior preserves its driver-focused ergonomics and bolster integrity. This is a mechanically sorted example optimized for the purist driver.",
      "price": 34500.0,
      "reputation": 0.4,
